					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>Records a gift of land in Śāsanamaṅgalam in Viḷā-nāḍu for food offerings on the occasion of the bathing ceremony of the god on the day of Rōhiṇī, the day of <hi rend="italic">tirumuḷaippuḻudi</hi> during the Paṅguṉi-Uttiram festival by Āchchiyaṉ-Bhaṭṭaṉ <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Śrī Vāsudēvaṉ, a <hi rend="italic">brahmādhirāja</hi> of Peruveṅgūr in Viḷā-nāḍu. This record is dated in the 39th year (945-46 A.D.) of the reign of Parāntaka I. cf. No. 9 below.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
